1
00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:02,630
[The theme is handmade]

2
00:00:00,190 --> 00:00:01,750
Make Dubai chewy cookies.

3
00:00:01,750 --> 00:00:02,970
How about making desserts?

4
00:00:02,970 --> 00:00:04,340
Hello, express delivery for you.

5
00:00:03,070 --> 00:00:08,560
[Manito Gift-Giving Battle that lasted 2 days]

6
00:00:04,340 --> 00:00:05,780
Who are you? Who are you?

7
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:06,980
Why are you running so fast?

8
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:08,490
I told you I could do it!

9
00:00:08,490 --> 00:00:10,260
See! She came and left!

10
00:00:08,890 --> 00:00:11,370
[What's their new mission?]

11
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:11,410
What's with him?

12
00:00:11,390 --> 00:00:13,790
[HQ: To become an official member
of Manito Club,]

13
00:00:13,940 --> 00:00:14,940
[HQ: you have to share the warmth]

14
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:16,090
[HQ: you received from each other]

15
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,840
[HQ: with the rest of the world
through a Secret Manito mission.]

16
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:20,220
Are we a team?

17
00:00:19,150 --> 00:00:20,260
[The 6 gathered here are a team]

18
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:21,410
The location?

19
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:22,280
[Who's the recipient of the Secret Manito gift?]

20
00:00:21,410 --> 00:00:22,360
Where is it?

21
00:00:22,650 --> 00:00:24,600
[Secret Manito: Bucheon Fire Station]

22
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:24,820
Bucheon Fire Station.

23
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,220
[What do they need?]

24
00:00:24,820 --> 00:00:26,150
Let's do what they need.

25
00:00:26,150 --> 00:00:29,940
I've seen a lot of footage of them
being dispatched during mealtimes.

26
00:00:26,630 --> 00:00:29,870
[Firefighters who are frequently dispatched
even during mealtimes]

27
00:00:29,940 --> 00:00:31,420
Let's cook for them.

28
00:00:31,420 --> 00:00:32,950
We can make supper for them.

29
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,930
[How about making something new?]

30
00:00:34,980 --> 00:00:37,940
It should be crispy. I'm stir-frying it.

31
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:36,680
[Made by Younjung: upgraded Dubai chewy cookies]

32
00:00:36,890 --> 00:00:39,450
[Stir-frying kadayif excitedly]

33
00:00:37,940 --> 00:00:39,250
You're good at it!

34
00:00:39,250 --> 00:00:40,820
Since there are pistachios,

35
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:43,250
[Contributing novel ideas]

36
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:43,030
how about putting a few pistachios
before adding the cream?

37
00:00:43,030 --> 00:00:44,410
A Manito version.

38
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:45,460
[Manito Club's Dubai chewy puffs has been created]

39
00:00:44,410 --> 00:00:45,590
Put rice cakes in it.

40
00:00:45,590 --> 00:00:47,050
-Rice cakes? -Yeah.

41
00:00:47,260 --> 00:00:48,730
[I was thinking about beef patties.]

42
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:50,610
Add an abalone in it.

43
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:52,570
[Add abalone for an energy boost]

44
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:52,650
He did a good job.

45
00:00:52,650 --> 00:00:54,120
Do you usually cook?

46
00:00:52,770 --> 00:00:56,960
[An expert at pan-frying meat]

47
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:56,160
I like cooking.

48
00:00:57,060 --> 00:00:58,320
It looks so yummy.

49
00:00:57,410 --> 00:00:59,520
[Made by Hae-in: Abalone Beef Patties]

50
00:00:58,320 --> 00:00:59,540
It looks so yummy.

51
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:00,880
[How about knife-cut noodles?]

52
00:01:01,010 --> 00:01:02,810
How about Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles?

53
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:02,330
[Main course of the nourishing meal]

54
00:01:02,580 --> 00:01:05,290
[Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles:
chock-full of nourishing ingredients]

55
00:01:03,810 --> 00:01:04,410
Is that octopus?

56
00:01:04,410 --> 00:01:05,620
Great, perfect.

57
00:01:05,450 --> 00:01:06,900
[Breathtaking sight that makes your mouth water]

58
00:01:05,620 --> 00:01:07,010
Wow, Yoon Namno.

59
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,200
[Eggs are also nourishing (?)]

60
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:08,760
Put one more here.

61
00:01:09,340 --> 00:01:10,660
[Chewing]

62
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,840
Can you get me a pot of this size?

63
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:12,520
[(Nods)]

64
00:01:12,610 --> 00:01:14,080
[(Caught ingesting nourishment)]

65
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:16,110
[Made by Jinkyung: well-simmered broth]

66
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:16,260
It's perfect.

67
00:01:16,260 --> 00:01:19,200
If we put effort into plating
to provide a VIP experience,

68
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:19,130
[Meticulously prepared with warmth]

69
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:20,730
I think it'll be more moving.

70
00:01:19,320 --> 00:01:21,970
[A warm nutritious meal for the firefighters]

71
00:01:20,730 --> 00:01:22,150
OK, shall we set off?

72
00:01:22,130 --> 00:01:23,820
[On their way to check out the fire station!]

73
00:01:22,150 --> 00:01:23,070
It's here. Bucheon Fire Station.

74
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:23,830
We're here.

75
00:01:23,830 --> 00:01:27,350
Please come to the back door. I'll guide you in.

76
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:26,950
[Can they sneak in smoothly?]

77
00:01:27,350 --> 00:01:28,710
Go, go, go.

78
00:01:27,450 --> 00:01:30,690
[On the way to meet their Secret Manito]

79
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:30,530
I think this is the place.

80
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,530
[Oh? Oh!]

81
00:01:32,850 --> 00:01:34,509
[Jung Hae-in: Hello.]

82
00:01:34,759 --> 00:01:36,030
[Wait, he didn't make a heart sign!]

83
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:38,090
Make a heart sign.

84
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:40,060
[Decided on a "heart" secret code
to identify their helper]

85
00:01:38,090 --> 00:01:40,250
Then we'll know it's you, OK?

86
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:41,330
Hello.

87
00:01:41,590 --> 00:01:43,560
["Heart" secret code confirmed]

88
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:42,920
A heart sign.

89
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,690
He did it.

90
00:01:43,690 --> 00:01:44,680
Hello.

91
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:46,970
[Successfully meet their helper]

92
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:46,970
This way, please.

93
00:01:46,990 --> 00:01:49,640
Be quiet! Be quiet!

94
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:51,410
[Following the helper to enter the station]

95
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:54,640
[Employees on duty still at work inside]

96
00:01:57,780 --> 00:01:59,759
[Stealthily]

97
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:02,490
We didn't disguise ourselves.

98
00:02:02,490 --> 00:02:03,960
[We are completely defenseless...]

99
00:02:04,140 --> 00:02:05,320
-Yeah. -We mustn't be caught.

100
00:02:04,530 --> 00:02:06,780
[Emergency disguise]

101
00:02:07,330 --> 00:02:10,300
[Moving to a safe place deep inside]

102
00:02:10,699 --> 00:02:12,040
-Hello. -Hello.

103
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:15,380
-Hello. -Hello.

104
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:15,350
[Staff lounge in the fire station's basement]

105
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:18,740
[Officially meet their helpers
in the fire station]

106
00:02:16,180 --> 00:02:17,460
-Here. -Hello.

107
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:21,180
[Hong Jinkyung: I didn't know
there was such a space in the fire station...]

108
00:02:21,180 --> 00:02:23,010
[Shh!]

109
00:02:23,270 --> 00:02:24,870
[Goodness...]

110
00:02:24,950 --> 00:02:26,200
Your hushing was louder.

111
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:28,020
[Too immersed in the situation]

112
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,030
He's suddenly so immersed.

113
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:29,480
Your "shh" was louder.

114
00:02:28,610 --> 00:02:32,650
[Anyway, they've successfully sneaked in]

115
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:30,930
Lift up your chairs.

116
00:02:30,930 --> 00:02:31,940
OK.

117
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:35,370
[Team Leader Shim Hoseong,
Fire Prevention and Life Safety Team]

118
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:34,270
Hello. Hello.

119
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:37,750
[Assistant Manager Choi Juyong,
Fire Prevention and Life Safety Team]

120
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,610
OK. OK. OK.

121
00:02:36,610 --> 00:02:37,890
We're set. We're set.

122
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:40,070
[Park Myungsoo: How many people
are there in your station?]

123
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,630
[Around 70 daytime admin staff members.]

124
00:02:44,579 --> 00:02:47,540
There are about 30 members available for dispatch.

125
00:02:47,540 --> 00:02:50,550
There are 30 to 40 members on duty right now.

126
00:02:49,390 --> 00:02:52,250
[Around 30 nighttime staff members]

127
00:02:50,550 --> 00:02:51,220
They're all in this building?

128
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:52,480
Yes, at work right now.

129
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:55,270
[Hong Jinkyung: When it's busy,
how many times are you dispatched in a day?]

130
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:58,040
There were 16 rescue cases...

131
00:02:58,060 --> 00:02:59,750
-Today? -Yes.

132
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:01,320
There were 14 fire cases.

133
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,480
Fires?

134
00:03:02,610 --> 00:03:06,200
[And about 65 emergency cases.]

135
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:05,620
65 cases?

136
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:08,680
We have 10 ambulances at our station.

137
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:10,120
[Shocking volume of emergency dispatch]

138
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:12,120
Bucheon is a small area,

139
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:14,450
[Bucheon has a high population density]

140
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,490
but it's densely populated.

141
00:03:14,490 --> 00:03:18,040
Within Gyeonggi Province, in 2025,

142
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:21,040
we had the second highest
number of rescue dispatches

143
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:24,380
and the highest number of emergency dispatches.

144
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:30,190
Compared nationwide, we also have
one of the highest numbers of dispatches.

145
00:03:30,570 --> 00:03:33,560
[(Helper) Choi Juyong: Our staff's
work fatigue levels are pretty high.]

146
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:35,510
[Yoon Namno: There was once...]

147
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:39,329
I had a really bad cut while slicing ginseng.

148
00:03:39,370 --> 00:03:41,340
A customer in the restaurant

149
00:03:41,370 --> 00:03:44,600
happened to work at a fire station.

150
00:03:44,790 --> 00:03:47,120
[Yoon Namno: They didn't hesitate at all.]

151
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,480
After emergency treatment,
they took me to the hospital right away,

152
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:51,440
even though they were on leave that day.

153
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:55,050
They stayed with me throughout the treatment.

154
00:03:52,260 --> 00:03:54,510
[A paramedic who stayed with him
until he was discharged]

155
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:59,329
It was like my parents were with me.

156
00:03:59,329 --> 00:04:00,890
It was very reassuring.

157
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:04,210
I'd forgotten about it,
but now that I'm here, I'm reminded of it.

158
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:05,710
[Hong Jinkyung: We'll put our gratitude]

159
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:09,360
[Hong Jinkyung: into today's food!]

160
00:04:10,530 --> 00:04:11,940
[What time do you have dinner?]

161
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:12,840
We usually have dinner at 5 PM.

162
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,250
You eat early.

163
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:16,269
[Yoon Namno: What time
do you usually have supper?]

164
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,970
[We don't eat if it's too late.]

165
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:22,370
[Usually at about 8 to 9 PM.]

166
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:20,700
8 to 9 PM.

167
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:22,900
Then 9 PM is better.

168
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:27,240
[By the way, we'll have to cook here...]

169
00:04:27,330 --> 00:04:28,250
We need to look at the kitchen.

170
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:31,400
[Today's actual purpose
is to inspect the kitchen]

171
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:31,470
Could we have a look at the kitchen?

172
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:34,390
I'm afraid our staff will get suspicious.

173
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:35,640
[A Secret Manito mission
where they can't take action blatantly]

174
00:04:34,390 --> 00:04:35,720
Right?

175
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:38,320
[Park Myungsoo: Let's make up a new show title.]

176
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:40,950
Pretend we're shooting another show?

177
00:04:41,270 --> 00:04:44,330
[Let's call it "Documentary Theater (?) Hero."]

178
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,830
-Hero... -It's a good name.

179
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:47,500
[Disguise as a documentary show]

180
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:45,830
"Hero" is good.

181
00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:47,470
Sounds good, "Hero."

182
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:50,960
[Kim Dohoon: Namno and I
will follow the 2 helpers]

183
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:55,580
[Kim Dohoon: and pretend
to be the documentary MCs.]

184
00:04:53,930 --> 00:04:55,710
We'll make excuses.

185
00:04:55,710 --> 00:04:59,390
You two have to be serious,
so it's convincing as a documentary.

186
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:01,960
-Have a serious attitude. -Yes.

187
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:05,020
Let's get moving then.

188
00:05:04,820 --> 00:05:06,700
Ah, I'm bad at lying.

189
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:09,710
Making commentary in secret
feels like a variety show though, haha.

190
00:05:09,690 --> 00:05:11,460
-You can do it! -You can do it!

191
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:13,620
[Since it's a documentary, don't smile too much.
You have a smiley face.]

192
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:15,530
-I have a smiley face? -Yes, don't smile.

193
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:16,820
I've never heard that in my life.

194
00:05:16,820 --> 00:05:18,560
Don't smile. Put on a serious face.

195
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,000
Don't smile too much.

196
00:05:18,650 --> 00:05:20,470
[(Actually quite happy to hear that)]

197
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:24,920
[A fan meeting before their infiltration]

198
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:23,550
We often talk about you over meals, Actress Go.

199
00:05:23,550 --> 00:05:25,090
-Really? -Yes.

200
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:26,400
[Go Younjung: Thank you for watching my drama.]

201
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,610
[Cha Muhee, Ddo Rami.]

202
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:30,570
[Not "Ddo" like crazy, but Do Rami.]

203
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:30,700
-Do Rami. -Do Rami.

204
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:31,940
[I've watched up to Episode 11.]

205
00:05:31,970 --> 00:05:33,150
Really? Only 1 episode left.

206
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:34,500
Only the finale left.

207
00:05:34,650 --> 00:05:35,840
[(Joking) It's a sad ending.]

208
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:38,270
Really? I was hoping for a happy ending.

209
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:38,610
[Shocked]

210
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,070
[Go Younjung: I want to go up
(for the inspection),]

211
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:42,740
[Go Younjung: but news about
me doing this show was released.]

212
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,350
It'll be total chaos if you show up.

213
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:45,750
[She can only wait inside so they're not exposed]

214
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:49,940
[119 Bucheon Fire Station]
[A proper tour of the station]

215
00:05:45,909 --> 00:05:47,280
Let's visit the rescue team first.

216
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:49,360
-Let's go. -Please follow me.

217
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:56,080
[First, visit the rescue team
in the annex building]

218
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:52,270
It's not far from here.

219
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:54,400
About 10 meters, about 5 meters.

220
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,260
-It's right beside it. -Yes.

221
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:59,600
[Monitoring the real-time situation
in the lounge]

222
00:05:58,290 --> 00:05:59,440
We can see them.

223
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:05,060
[Rescue team]

224
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,290
[The fire trucks are so cool!]

225
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:10,920
[The dispatch alarm suddenly rings]

226
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,740
[They're being dispatched now.]

227
00:06:18,710 --> 00:06:21,390
They got a report.

228
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:23,660
[Dispatch alarm that's also heard in the lounge]

229
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:24,280
Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!

230
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:26,310
There are really so many rescue reports.

231
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,460
Please set off now.

232
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:31,240
[The rescue team sets off swiftly]

233
00:06:37,780 --> 00:06:38,930
What do we do? Hide?

234
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:40,140
[Surprised]

235
00:06:38,930 --> 00:06:39,659
OMG.

236
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:43,310
[We're here to make a documentary.]

237
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:42,130
Yeah, we're fine.

238
00:06:42,130 --> 00:06:43,610
-We don't have to hide. -No need to hide.

239
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:46,720
[Yoon Namno: Because I'm a coward...]

240
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:46,909
Am I about to see this with my own eyes?

241
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:50,290
[It's canceled.]

242
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,510
-Canceled? -Yes.

243
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:52,840
Someone reported it and then canceled it.

244
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:53,810
[Fortunately, the call was cancelled]

245
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:56,720
[Relieved, they enter the rescue team's premises]

246
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:56,290
-Hello. -Hello.

247
00:06:57,190 --> 00:07:00,240
[The staff return to the office and regroup]

248
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:05,290
[Another dispatch
after barely catching their breaths]

249
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,500
Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!

250
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,690
Respected by many...

251
00:07:07,690 --> 00:07:08,730
There are many reasons.

252
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,550
[The alarm rings again]

253
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:10,870
There's another dispatch.

254
00:07:12,230 --> 00:07:13,850
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: Stay close to the wall.]

255
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,280
[S-Should we leave first?]

256
00:07:14,780 --> 00:07:17,150
-Yes, go downstairs first. -Make way for them.

257
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:18,170
[Wait outside, so they don't disrupt the dispatch]

258
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:21,160
It's happened twice in 5 minutes.

259
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:22,720
Time to set off!

260
00:07:22,130 --> 00:07:26,490
[The rescue team comes out in a hurry again]

261
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:30,030
[Moves out immediately]

262
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,620
[Yoon Namno: Those who came downstairs]

263
00:07:31,770 --> 00:07:34,120
[Yoon Namno: were those
who went upstairs just now, right?]

264
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,720
Yes.

265
00:07:34,950 --> 00:07:36,360
[They really set off right away.]

266
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,460
-It took less than 10 seconds, right? -Yes.

267
00:07:38,460 --> 00:07:40,210
Really fast.

268
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:42,880
-Hello. -Hello.

269
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:44,330
[Wearing earbuds to communicate with
the other cast members, as they enter the office]

270
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,300
-Hello. -They're here for

271
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:46,620
the documentary "Hero."

272
00:07:46,620 --> 00:07:52,060
We're... like exploring... like what happens
over the course of 24 hours

273
00:07:46,620 --> 00:07:51,670
[Trying to interview the remaining employees]

274
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:53,650
in the fire station.

275
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:56,060
[A bit awkward, but quite convincing]

276
00:07:53,650 --> 00:07:55,230
That's what we're doing.

277
00:07:56,330 --> 00:08:00,780
[Kim Dohoon: We're going to record
the narration later. So we came in person.]

278
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,930
-We have to see it with our own eyes. -Yes.

279
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:04,190
Good job. They're doing good.

280
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:07,890
They'll check out
the daily routine of firefighters

281
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,370
[Kim Daejoong, Leader of Rescue Team 3]

282
00:08:06,910 --> 00:08:09,570
[Park Heesoo, Rescue Team 3]

283
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:09,590
and ask some questions.

284
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,910
[To apply to be rescue team members,]

285
00:08:12,290 --> 00:08:18,190
[you need at least 2 years
of experience in the special forces]

286
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:21,140
[You're all really handsome.]

287
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:22,770
No, no.

288
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:23,620
[Shy]

289
00:08:24,220 --> 00:08:28,720
[Q. What do you hope
citizens can offer help with?]

290
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:30,940
[Just like today, we came back after a mission.]

291
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,470
[Kim Daejoong: We couldn't get through
because of an illegally parked car.]

292
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:35,260
We called them, but they didn't answer.

293
00:08:35,260 --> 00:08:37,200
After calling many times, he finally picked up.

294
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,390
[Kim Daejoong: In a very cold tone,
he said he'll drive it out now.]

295
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:40,669
[But he didn't show up.]

296
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:44,320
[Kim Daejoong: So we had to request
for legally parked cars to make way for us.]

297
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:48,620
[That was really infuriating.]

298
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:47,680
Of course. In such a situation.

299
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:48,860
It made me mad.

300
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:52,040
[Q. Do you have any taboos?]

301
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:54,780
[Not really.]

302
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:56,530
But there are things that we don't say.

303
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:57,770
[Like, why it's so quiet today?]

304
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:59,390
[Please don't say that.]

305
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:01,380
Really? Sorry.

306
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:00,670
[Oops...]

307
00:09:01,210 --> 00:09:04,850
[Forbidden words in the fire station]

308
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:03,000
Oh, I see.

309
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,660
We don't say things like that.

310
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:10,150
Based on the severity of the emergency,

311
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,090
is the alarm different?

312
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:14,530
Like Code Blue in the hospital.

313
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,300
[Kim Dohoon: There's something
I've been curious about.]

314
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:17,600
[Kim Dohoon: Can I ask another question?]

315
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:23,740
[Kim Dohoon: Is there a different alarm
according to the severity of the situation?]

316
00:09:23,550 --> 00:09:25,150
-Like hospitals... -They're all different.

317
00:09:25,150 --> 00:09:28,060
One for fires, one for rescues,
and one for emergencies.

318
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:30,710
[The dispatch alarms that ring
dozens of times a day]

319
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:34,870
[The difference between
the fire, rescue, and emergency alarm]

320
00:09:36,380 --> 00:09:40,990
[The 1st dispatch alarm: begins solemnly]

321
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,210
[Fire dispatch! Fire dispatch!]

322
00:09:43,970 --> 00:09:48,140
[Fires that can result in major casualties
even with a slight delay]

323
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:52,300
Something happened on Basement One.

324
00:09:49,050 --> 00:09:54,370
[In charge of putting out fires,
rescue, and risk elimination]

325
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,500
The smell is from Basement One.

326
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:59,050
[The fire team
who wipes out the panic in the city]

327
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:03,320
As assistance on the fire scene...

328
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,920
[Gets up] [Gets up]

329
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:06,510
[The 2nd dispatch alarm: most frequently heard]

330
00:10:07,230 --> 00:10:09,450
[Rescue dispatch! Rescue Dispatch!]

331
00:10:10,330 --> 00:10:14,980
[In charge of emergency patients
and hospital transportation]

332
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:19,640
[The rescue team rushes
to stay within the golden hour]

333
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:24,620
[The 3rd dispatch alarm: the last one]

334
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:26,350
[Rescue dispatch!]

335
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:30,890
[In charge of lifesaving and risk elimination]

336
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:34,610
[The rescue team who saves lives
on the front lines]

337
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:37,860
[Jung Hae-in: These are things
the viewers probably didn't know.]

338
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:39,620
[I didn't know either!]

339
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:44,920
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: He's a chef,
so he's the most curious about what we eat.]

340
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,060
I said we all eat differently.

341
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:46,860
[We usually eat whatever we have, haha.]

342
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:48,060
[Something that's fast.]

343
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,160
[Things we can eat later
even if we leave it to go on missions.]

344
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:52,880
[A menu suited to irregular dispatches]

345
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:53,100
That's what we usually eat.

346
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:57,130
-Enjoy. -Enjoy.

347
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:56,630
[Late at night, in the rescue team's office]

348
00:10:57,510 --> 00:11:02,520
[Today's supper is fried chicken and pizza]

349
00:10:59,070 --> 00:11:00,950
I should have ordered more.

350
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:02,600
It's OK. I'll just eat less.

351
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,510
There's instant noodles too.

352
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:07,680
[Kim Daejoong: Even if we can't finish the pizza
and fried chicken, we can eat it when we return.]

353
00:11:07,830 --> 00:11:10,820
[Kim Daejoong: Other than instant noodles,
we don't have food with soups.]

354
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:14,800
It's cheap, so we won't feel wasteful
even if we don't get to finish it.

355
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:15,740
[Restricted supper choices
because of frequent dispatches]

356
00:11:18,930 --> 00:11:25,820
[Free time is only temporary;
the bell rings again]

357
00:11:23,610 --> 00:11:25,800
Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!

358
00:11:27,310 --> 00:11:29,310
[Yoon Namno: If you're dispatched
in the middle of eating,]

359
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:31,200
[Yoon Namno: I feel like
your appetite will be ruined.]

360
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:33,470
I think so too.

361
00:11:31,430 --> 00:11:33,700
[That's right.]

362
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:35,550
Oh, I see.

363
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,600
[Jung Hae-in: But their interview]

364
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:37,870
[is done well like a documentary.]

365
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,850
[I agree.]

366
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:39,870
Like a documentary.

367
00:11:39,870 --> 00:11:41,050
You have great bodies.

368
00:11:40,390 --> 00:11:44,120
[The first round of interviews
went better than expected]

369
00:11:41,050 --> 00:11:41,790
I'm jealous.

370
00:11:41,790 --> 00:11:44,550
-Thank you. -Here.

371
00:11:47,070 --> 00:11:50,910
Is this exclusive to this team, or...

372
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:54,680
[The slogan is pasted everywhere]

373
00:11:54,690 --> 00:11:56,110
[First In Last Out]
[Gyeonggi Province Fire Station]

374
00:11:56,130 --> 00:12:00,060
[First In Last Out]
[The first to go in; the last to come out]

375
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:08,480
[For the safety of the citizens,
with a strong sense of duty,]

376
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:14,710
[they go in first and come out last]

377
00:12:14,830 --> 00:12:17,160
First in; last out.

378
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:22,310
[The first to go in; the last to come out.]

379
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:23,110
So cool. So solemn.

380
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:25,510
-The last to come out. -The last to come out.

381
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:28,430
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
But it's not easy to stick to it.]

382
00:12:28,570 --> 00:12:30,720
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
To go in first and come out last.]

383
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,290
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: So we have to
strengthen our resolve all the time.]

384
00:12:33,530 --> 00:12:36,940
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: It is
what's in the "Firefighters' Prayer."]

385
00:12:36,970 --> 00:12:39,830
[Firefighters' Prayer:
God! When I'm summoned, no matter how big
the fire, please give me strength to save a life.
Let me embrace a child
and save a frightened elder before it's too late.]

386
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:38,990
We think about it over and over again,

387
00:12:38,990 --> 00:12:40,470
to try our best to do as it says.

388
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:43,580
[Give me the ability to ensure safety
at all times, to hear the weakest screams,
and put out fires quickly and efficiently.]

389
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:43,980
It's hard for us too.

390
00:12:43,770 --> 00:12:46,940
[Let me fulfill my duty to do my best
to protect every life and property.]

391
00:12:43,980 --> 00:12:46,250
We're scared too.

392
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:49,680
But if we don't do it, no one will.

393
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:53,650
[If fate be it that my life ends,
may God's grace bless my spouse and family.]

394
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:52,910
Of course I'm scared.

395
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:58,170
I'm lying if I say I'm not scared.

396
00:12:54,130 --> 00:12:58,030
[Lee Takjoon, Fire Extinguishing Team 3]

397
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:04,330
[I'm scared.]

398
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:06,350
[Lee Takjoon: Arriving at the scene,]

399
00:13:08,330 --> 00:13:11,440
[Lee Takjoon: the moment I see the fire,
I get scared.]

400
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:14,530
[Lee Takjoon: The team leaders
usually go in first.]

401
00:13:15,490 --> 00:13:17,630
[I can only trust them and follow them.]

402
00:13:17,970 --> 00:13:20,080
[Lee Yoseob: I can't see anything inside.]

403
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:22,300
[Lee Yoseob: Not even things in front of me.]

404
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:25,500
[Lee Yoseob: I can only rely on the person
in front of me and move forward.]

405
00:13:25,650 --> 00:13:27,930
Yes, they're my lifeline.

406
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:28,280
[Colleagues are lifelines]

407
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,790
[Kang Yeonik: If the team leader
hesitates at the beginning,]

408
00:13:30,930 --> 00:13:32,800
[Kang Yeonik: the others will also hesitate.]

409
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:36,910
[Kang Yeonik: So the team leaders
must lead by example.]

410
00:13:37,180 --> 00:13:41,950
[Jo Seondeok: I'm the center director,
in charge of command and other tasks.]

411
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:46,870
[Jo Seondeok: If I make a wrong judgment
or give a wrong order,]

412
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:48,660
[Jo Seondeok: more citizens may get hurt.]

413
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,910
[Jo Seondeok: Or the fire might spread.]

414
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:56,050
[My judgment may jeopardize
the lives of my colleagues.]

415
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:58,030
This is what's really tough.

416
00:13:57,600 --> 00:14:01,370
[Always bearing a heavy sense of responsibility]

417
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:02,740
It's a constant heavy burden inside.

418
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:04,170
I keep thinking about this.

419
00:14:04,170 --> 00:14:06,560
I go in first and I come out last.

420
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:09,890
I'm sure the team leaders feel it the most.

421
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,100
This is the leader, the rescue team leader.

422
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:14,200
-Just now we... -Rescue Team Leader.

423
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:16,200
[Salute]

424
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,200
How do we salute? Do we say "victory"?

425
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,360
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
We usually say "safety."]

426
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:20,970
[1, 2, 3. Safety slogan (?)]

427
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:23,680
-Safety! -Safety!

428
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:24,680
[(Rescue team leader) Kim Geonwon: Safety!]

429
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:25,620
-Thank you. -Have a safe drive home!

430
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:27,290
[Thank you for your hard work!]

431
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,880
Have a safe drive home!

432
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:32,170
-Isn't this nice? -So this is the fitness room.

433
00:14:32,170 --> 00:14:33,960
-Hello. -Hello.

434
00:14:32,810 --> 00:14:36,760
[Fitness Room]

435
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,770
We have better facilities than other departments.

436
00:14:36,770 --> 00:14:39,240
I relieve stress through exercise.

437
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:41,690
[Members who spare time to stay in shape]

438
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:41,030
You don't rest but exercise.

439
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:42,690
Many of them do that.

440
00:14:43,020 --> 00:14:45,430
[It's the smell of tough man.]

441
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,210
[Hello.]

442
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:49,520
-Hello. -Hello.

443
00:14:48,630 --> 00:14:51,500
[Lee Yoseob, Fire Extinguishing Team 3]

444
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:51,430
We're here for the documentary "Hero."

445
00:14:51,430 --> 00:14:53,230
He has a great body.

446
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:58,570
[Namno! Touch the biceps
of the person in front of you.]

447
00:14:57,670 --> 00:14:59,160
Touch his biceps.

448
00:14:58,910 --> 00:15:01,060
[Quivering lips]

449
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:03,780
[About to burst out laughing]

450
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:06,480
-Since he loves working out. -He's going.

451
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:06,490
[Slightly hesitant]

452
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,690
He's doing it.

453
00:15:07,550 --> 00:15:08,970
[Woah!]

454
00:15:09,270 --> 00:15:11,100
[Wow, amazing.]

455
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,010
No, no. Thank you.

456
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:15,490
[Ask him to make a few cool poses.]

457
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:15,600
Make some cool poses.

458
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:18,230
[What if we're exposed?]

459
00:15:16,610 --> 00:15:18,310
"Make a few cool poses."

460
00:15:18,590 --> 00:15:20,180
[Then hang on his biceps.]

461
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,990
[Pft]

462
00:15:20,230 --> 00:15:21,660
Go on.

463
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,040
Go on!

464
00:15:24,370 --> 00:15:26,950
[Hahaha] [Hahaha] [Hahaha]

465
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:25,930
-He... Please make a few cool poses.

466
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:28,950
He's holding back his laughter.

467
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,660
[Hahaha] [Hahaha]

468
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:31,230
[Hahaha] [Hahaha]

469
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:32,110
-He can't keep his laughter in!
-And hang on his biceps.

470
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:33,400
[Struggling]

471
00:15:32,110 --> 00:15:35,390
Can you do a pose to show us your biceps?

472
00:15:35,390 --> 00:15:38,010
-Could he... -Could I hang on them?

473
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:43,220
[If you wish]

474
00:15:42,350 --> 00:15:44,140
OMG.

475
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,520
[Wow!]

476
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,390
[Trembling]

477
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:51,310
[His feet are off the ground!]

478
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:54,030
[Falls immediately]

479
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:57,630
[Even muscular men
can't withstand the weight of Namno]

480
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:56,730
He failed.

481
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,880
OMG.

482
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:02,900
Anyway, after working out...

483
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,810
[Kim Dohoon: Those into fitness]

484
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:04,720
[Kim Dohoon: always say nutrition
is part of working out.]

485
00:16:04,370 --> 00:16:05,030
Yes, that's right.

486
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:07,050
[Kim Dohoon: What do you eat after working out?]

487
00:16:07,390 --> 00:16:10,070
[Lee Yoseob: I don't follow a diet plan.]

488
00:16:09,540 --> 00:16:11,940
I just eat a lot.

489
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:13,460
-Eat a lot? -Yeah.

490
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,740
[Yoon Namno: To people like you,
who have burly bodies...]

491
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:20,980
What protein food would you recommend?

492
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,780
-I like beef. -Beef...

493
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:27,120
-So you like beef patties too, right? -Yes, I do.

494
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:27,120
[Subtly hinting]

495
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,120
I see.

496
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:29,150
[Score]

497
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,010
All the best!

498
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:33,090
[Weight loss]

499
00:16:30,010 --> 00:16:31,500
All the best. Thank you for your hard work.

500
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:32,810
Thank you.

501
00:16:33,550 --> 00:16:36,040
[Central 119 Security Center]

502
00:16:34,010 --> 00:16:35,440
Hello.

503
00:16:36,260 --> 00:16:37,220
Hello.

504
00:16:37,650 --> 00:16:40,050
[119] [Bucheon Fire Station]
[Central 119 Security Center]

505
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,800
[Fire, Rescue, Emergency]

506
00:16:43,020 --> 00:16:45,090
[Fire]

507
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:46,860
[Emergency]

508
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,690
[Life Safety]

509
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:52,700
[Busiest department in Bucheon Fire Station]

510
00:16:53,230 --> 00:16:55,980
[(Helper) Choi Juyong:
The center director is here.]

511
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:58,830
-Hello. -Hello.

512
00:16:58,830 --> 00:17:02,720
