958
00:32:43,860 --> 00:32:46,420
[But honestly... pouring cooking oil isn't the kind of thing
you should ask the head chef to do.]

959
00:32:46,420 --> 00:32:49,980
[Ah... Sorry...]

960
00:32:50,140 --> 00:32:51,220
I'm the head chef, you know.

961
00:32:50,260 --> 00:32:52,540
[Clear hierarchy in the kitchen]

962
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:54,580
[Yoon Namno/Head Chef] [Kim Dohoon/Youngest Chef]

963
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:54,790
You're the youngest, and I'm the head chef.

964
00:32:54,790 --> 00:32:56,140
-So... -Then I...

965
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:56,580
[The amused sous-chef (?)]

966
00:32:56,620 --> 00:32:58,700
[Kim Dohoon/Youngest Chef: I guess this is what they call
"the student surpassing the teacher" (?)]

967
00:32:59,860 --> 00:33:02,980
[A different interpretation of "student surpasses the teacher"]

968
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,710
That's not what that phrase means.

969
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:05,720
I used to be most afraid of strangers, but you...

970
00:33:05,260 --> 00:33:09,460
[Lively] [There's a little tiger in the kitchen...]

971
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:09,900
They say the most dangerous person is the one who doesn't know any better.

972
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:11,620
Looks like it's ready. Let's put it in.

973
00:33:11,620 --> 00:33:16,340
[Huge] [The patty is even bigger than during practice]

974
00:33:20,860 --> 00:33:22,500
[Beef patty sizzling in the pan]

975
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:23,740
[Sss...]

976
00:33:23,740 --> 00:33:28,340
[Jung Hae-in: But is it fine that we don't add pepper to the beef patties?]

977
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:26,520
-We don't need to add pepper? -Eh?

978
00:33:28,380 --> 00:33:30,420
[Pepper?]

979
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:34,820
[Namno runs off]

980
00:33:34,820 --> 00:33:36,700
[Kim Dohoon: We should add pepper?]

981
00:33:35,060 --> 00:33:37,460
-We should add pepper? -Pepper, pepper...

982
00:33:39,180 --> 00:33:43,780
[Jung Hae-in (Meat Expert): Pepper really makes the patties taste better.]

983
00:33:43,780 --> 00:33:46,820
[Jung Hae-in: Because I take meat very seriously.]

984
00:33:46,820 --> 00:33:48,620
[Why didn't you say so earlier? We need to add pepper.]

985
00:33:48,700 --> 00:33:50,020
[Eh?]

986
00:33:50,220 --> 00:33:51,300
[Why didn't you say earlier?]

987
00:33:51,460 --> 00:33:52,500
[I'm sorry.]

988
00:33:53,060 --> 00:33:55,700
I guess I didn't surpass my teacher after all.

989
00:33:56,220 --> 00:33:57,900
Wow, Hae-in, good thing you noticed.

990
00:33:58,300 --> 00:34:00,060
["Surpassing the teacher" moment]

991
00:33:58,350 --> 00:33:59,170
-OK. OK. -Hm.

992
00:33:59,660 --> 00:34:00,300
Namno.

993
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:02,330
-So we do need pepper. -Yes.

994
00:34:01,500 --> 00:34:03,860
[Sprinkling pepper]

995
00:34:04,540 --> 00:34:09,739
[Wait... Does that mean I have to mix it again?]
[What? That's how kitchens work—you just do what you're told.]

996
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:06,680
What?

997
00:34:09,290 --> 00:34:10,020
Ah, ok.

998
00:34:10,100 --> 00:34:12,780
[Actually, we could've just done this all at once from the start.]

999
00:34:10,139 --> 00:34:13,110
-Actually, we could've just done this all at once from the start.
-Right, right.

1000
00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:15,170
-It's all my fault. -Put more pepper in the pan.

1001
00:34:13,179 --> 00:34:16,780
[It's the fault of the person in charge of the beef patties anyway]

1002
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:20,420
